<p><lb n="1"/>pūrvva liṅāv<unclear>·</unclear> <unclear cert="low">nī</unclear></p>
         </div>
<!-- 
Salomé suggests pūrvva liṅait· (4/5)
And she comments
In C. 148, there is one occurence of the word liṅait (l. d1) meaning "exterior, outside" as well, and two of the word paliṅait (l. C13 et d4).
The upward stroke attached to the top of -ṅa, and followed by an unclear (downward) hook makes me think of the possibility of the vowel -ai.
As for the following consonnant, I read a -ta + virāma (more than a -va + virāma).
As for the following sign, could it be a number, such as a 4 or a 5? Or just a punctuation sign?
 -->
         <div type="apparatus"/>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
 	<p>This is the east outside.</p>
         </div>
